29/01/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- During a meeting Wednesday (28 January) with Greek Ambassador Pantelis Carabassis, Albanian Finance Minister Arben Malaj called on Greece to provide more financial support to Albanian companies. 
Malaj praised the successful co-operation between the two countries and the support provided so far. 
He added that the government is committed to boosting its capacity for credit utilisation and asked Athens to increase its lending.
In other news, representatives of Albania, Kosovo and UNMIK met on Wednesday and agreed to establish a joint commission to monitor implementation of the free trade agreement between the neighbours. 
(Korrieri, Koha Jone - 29/01/04; ATA - 28/01/04)
